Definition: lacking physical movement skills, especially with the hands
Example: a bumbling mechanic; a bungling performance; ham-handed governmental interference; could scarcely empty a scuttle of ashes, so handless was the poor creature- Mary H. Vorse
Synonyms: bungling, butterfingered, ham-fisted, ham-handed, handless, heavy-handed, left-handed, lacking, physical, movement, skills, especially, with, the, hands, a, mechanic, performance, governmental, interference, could, scarcely, empty, scuttle, of, ashes, so, was, poor, creature, -, Mary, H, Vorse
Category: adj.all
